HEADWORD: Mephitical
<hw>Me*phit"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mephiticus</ets>, fr.
<ets>mephitis</ets> mephitis: cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧phitique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Tending to destroy
life; poisonous; noxious; <as>as, <ex>mephitic</ex> exhalations;
<ex>mephitic</ex> regions.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Offensive to the smell; <as>as, <ex>mephitic</ex>
odors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mephitic air</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>carbon
dioxide; -- so called because of its deadly suffocating power. See
<cref>Carbonic acid</cref>, under <er>Carbonic</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mephitinae</ent>⟦br⟧
